Driskel ubunto from scratch notes.  Note change to regular install at end, python3 setup.py install --user

1. Burn ISO of ubuntu to USB drive via etcher
2. Load USB into new machine
3. Reboot or turn on computer “Delete” key will get you into bios
4. Set USB - SanDisk to boot device 1 and then install
5. Create user:
    username: pinball
    password: pinball
6. DO NOT INSTALL AUTO UPDATES
Configure:
1. Terminal
cd ~
ssh-keygen -t ed22519 -C “emailaddress”
copy contents of .ssh/id_ed25519.pub
SIGN INTO GITHUB
  Settings
    SSH and GPG Keys
    and create a new key “PIN” and copy contents
mkdir pinball
mkdir pinball/install
sudo apt install git
git config --global user.name “me”
git config --global user.email “email”
sudo apt install openssh-server
CHECK TO SEE IF IT IS RUNNING
sudo systemctl status sshd
FIREFOX
    change no metric to developers
    change download directory to ~/pinball/install
cd ~/pinball/
git clone git@github.com/driskel/pinball_games.git
cd ~/pinball/pinball_games/ubuntu_install
sudo cp 00-teensy.rules /etc/udev/rules.d/
sudo reboot
download MPF
cd to MPF folder
Change in the install-proc:
    cd pypinproc
    sudo python3 setup.py install
to:
   cd pypinproc
   python3 setup.py install --user
install MPF and Libpinproc for Multimorphic
    https://docs.missionpinball.org/en/latest/install/linux/index.html
INSTALL VSCODE
